column1: Philadelphia Original Cream Cheese traces its roots back to 1872, and it has been the standard of high quality cream cheese ever since. Today, it is made with five simple ingredients and is perfect for adding creaminess to recipes. You already love it for cheesecakes and dips, but be sure to give it a try for making creamy pasta sauce, delectable no-bake desserts, rich soups and much more. Local dairy farmers near Beaver Dam, WI and Lowville, NY supply Philly with fresh milk, which we combine with real cream. The entire process from farm to creamery takes just six days. But we don't stop at farm fresh milk and real cream. We also never add artificial preservatives, flavors or dyes in any of our cream cheese spreads. So in the end, everything just seems a little bit better with the creamy taste of Philly.

column1: Produced in the heart of the Brie area, our Artisan Brie is a regional cheese of quality that is made by hand using traditional methods. Our cheese artisan, through extensive research, is able to offer this pasteurized cows' milk artisan brie with an extraordinary flavor and appearance found in only the finest cow's milk cheeses. The cheese is carefully aged for two weeks. Its extraordinary full cream flavor is indeed spectacular. For a cheeseboard, serve this brie at room temperature with slices of pear and a glass of herbaceous, dry pinot grigio or a fruity weissbier.

column1: This pasteurized Manchego is from a family-owned company based outside of Cuenca, Spain. After three months of aging, it is nutty, creamy, and full-flavored. The taste is full and fills the entire mouth. There is a nice balance between acid up front and the rich finish.

column1: With a superbly creamy texture and a slightly sweet, earthy flavor, this Burrata is a welcome addition to any appetizer, cheese board, or entrée. Hailing from Wisconsin, this cheese is prepared to order using cow’s milk from Midwest farmers. Its delightfully silken texture comes from bathing unspun mozzarella curds in fresh heavy cream and then sealing this blend inside a fresh mozzarella skin. Each piece is hand-crafted for precision and stored in water to prevent spoilage.

column1: Grated Parmesan cheese, is a hard, nutty Italian cheese that is made from cow's milk. It is aged for at least two years to develop its distinctive flavor and texture, which are both complex and robust. Grated Parmesan cheese is a popular ingredient in Italian cuisine and is often used as a topping for pasta dishes, salads, soups, and pizzas. It has a granular texture that crumbles easily, and its intense flavor is perfect for adding depth and richness to a wide range of recipes.

column1: Calabro Fresh Ricotta Cone is a high-quality and fresh cheese made from the finest cow's milk. It is a classic Italian cheese that is known for its light and fluffy texture, creamy taste, and versatility in the kitchen. The fresh ricotta is made by heating the whey left over from the production of other cheeses, and then adding fresh whole milk to create a curd. The curd is then drained and molded into a cone shape, which makes it easy to slice and serve. Calabro Fresh Ricotta Cone is perfect for a wide range of culinary applications, such as using it as a filling for pastries, as a topping for pizzas and bruschetta, or as an ingredient in pasta dishes. It can also be used in desserts, such as cannolis, tiramisu, and cheesecake.

column1: This Gruyere King Cut Swiss Cheese Loaf is the culmination of centuries of Switzerland�s cheesemaking mastery. This cheese relies on fresh milk brought in twice daily from local farms, ensuring that you get the most high quality finished product. The cheese is then prepared in copper vats and left to mature in cellars, where expert cheesemakers closely watch the aging process for maximum flavor development. This gruyere boast hints of candied walnut as well as a touch of warm spice and dried fruits, resulting in a cheese that is just the slightest bit sweet with a luxuriously rich texture.

column1: Blue cheese crumbles are small pieces of blue cheese that have been crumbled or broken up for easy use in salads, dressings, and other dishes. Blue cheese is a type of cheese that is known for its distinctive, sharp flavor and creamy texture, with blue or green veins running through it. The crumbles are typically made from high-quality blue cheese, which is aged for several months to develop its characteristic flavor. They can be used to add a tangy, rich flavor to a wide variety of dishes, from salads and sandwiches to pizza and pasta.

column1: This 18-24 Month Parmesan Reggiano Cheese Wheel is edible proof that good things really do take time. This PDO cheese is crafted using cows milk from particular Italian regions including Parma and Bologna, allowing for a taste of tradition that is difficult to top. Aging yields an unmistakable sensation of umami and a robust nutty, vaguely fruity flavor. This cheese is lactose free and offers a hard, dense texture perfect for an indulgent snack or simple garnish. Pair with a glass of chilled Chianti or Sauvignon Blanc for a delightful after-dinner treat.

column1: Domestic Feta is a popular cheese that is known for its tangy and salty flavor and crumbly texture. Made from high-quality cow's milk, this cheese is carefully crafted to create a delicious and versatile ingredient that is perfect for a variety of dishes. Domestic Feta is a versatile cheese that can be used in a variety of dishes, including salads, pasta dishes, and sandwiches. It can also be used as a topping for pizza or added to omelets and frittatas for added flavor and richness.

column1: Cream cheese is a soft, spreadable cheese that is commonly used as a topping or filling for a variety of dishes. It is made by blending milk and cream with lactic acid bacteria to create a smooth and creamy texture. Cream cheese has a mild and slightly tangy flavor that pairs well with many other flavors and ingredients. It is often used as a spread on bagels or toast, as a filling in sandwiches and wraps, or as a base for dips and spreads. It is also used in baking recipes, such as cheesecakes and pastries, where it adds a rich and creamy texture.

column1: Grated parmesan cheese is a popular Italian-style cheese that has been finely grated, making it easier to use as an ingredient in various recipes. This cheese is made from cow's milk and has a hard, crumbly texture that's perfect for grating. Grated parmesan cheese has a nutty and slightly salty flavor, which makes it a popular ingredient in many Italian dishes, including pasta dishes, salads, and pizzas. It's also a great addition to soups, stews, and casseroles, as well as a variety of other recipes.

column1: Low moisture shredded mozzarella is a type of cheese that is made by partially drying fresh mozzarella cheese and then shredding it into small pieces. It has a lower moisture content than fresh mozzarella, which makes it firmer and more suitable for melting. It is commonly used in cooking and baking, particularly in Italian and American cuisine, and is a popular ingredient for making pizza, pasta dishes, casseroles, and other savory dishes. It has a mild, slightly tangy flavor and a stretchy texture when melted.

column1: Goat Cheese Crumbles are renowned for their unique, tangy flavor and creamy, crumbly texture. Each bite is a celebration of the distinctive taste that defines this exceptional cheese. These crumbles aren't just for salads; they're a versatile culinary companion. Sprinkle them over pizzas, incorporate them into creamy pasta sauces, or use them to create delectable appetizers that showcase the depth and authenticity of goat cheese. We believe in preserving the art of traditional cheese-making, and our Goat Cheese Crumbles are a testament to that commitment. Meticulously crafted in small batches, they embody the care, expertise, and authenticity that define quality cheese.

column1: Yellow shredded cheddar is a type of cheese that has been shredded into small, thin pieces. It is made from cow's milk and has a rich, tangy flavor. Yellow shredded cheddar is a versatile cheese that can be used in a variety of dishes. It is commonly used as a topping for tacos, nachos, and other Mexican dishes, as well as on top of baked potatoes, salads, and sandwiches. It can also be used in cooking, such as in macaroni and cheese, casseroles, and quiches.

column1: The Drunken Goat® is a mild and fruity semi-soft goat cheese from Jumilla, Spain. It is soaked in the traditional style wine of the region, Doble Pasta, which is made from the Monastrell grape. The cheese is aged for 60 days, so that you can still enjoy some of the wine’s flavors and the rind takes on an attractive violet hue. The Drunken Goat® is mild and smooth, not goaty, with a touch of fruitiness in the finish. It pairs well with a variety of wines and can be served on a cheese board or even as dessert.

column1: Gorgonzola Dolce is a type of Italian blue cheese that is known for its rich, creamy texture and sweet, mild flavor. It is made from cow's milk and is aged for a short period of time, which results in a softer and milder flavor compared to other blue cheeses. Gorgonzola Dolce is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of culinary applications. It is often crumbled and used as a topping for salads and pizzas, or served on a cheese platter with other types of cheese and accompaniments. It can also be used in sauces, dressings, and dips, or melted into a risotto or pasta dish.

column1: Kolios Greek Feta is a type of cheese that is made from sheep's milk and is a staple of Greek cuisine. It is a white, crumbly cheese with a slightly salty taste and tangy flavor. The cheese is made using traditional methods and is aged in brine for a minimum of two months, which helps to enhance its flavor and texture. Kolios Greek Feta can be used in a variety of dishes such as salads, sandwiches, and pastas, and is often served with olives, tomatoes, and other Mediterranean ingredients.

column1: This unique cheese has been granted a Denomination of Protected Origin Certification to guarantee its traditional qualities. It is made with pasteurized cow's milk that is aged and hand-washed weekly over a ripening period of 50 days. The end result has a strong aroma but mild, creamy taste with a unique fruity tang and buttery soft texture beneath an inedible straw-colored crust. Taleggio is an excellent dessert cheese, pairing well with a glass of structured, fruity Merlot or a malty Belgian beer.

column1: Grana Padano cheese is a hard, slow-ripened cheese made from partially skimmed cow's milk. It is similar in texture and flavor to Parmesan cheese but has a slightly nuttier taste. Grana Padano is typically aged for 18-24 months and has a granular, crumbly texture with a golden rind. It is often used as a table cheese, grated over pasta or soups, or served as a dessert cheese. Grana Padano is a popular Italian cheese and is widely used in cooking and food preparation.

column1: This award-winning Humboldt Fog Goat Cheese is handcrafted and soft-ripened for a deliciously rich, smooth bite. Buttermilk and fresh cream flavors dominate, complemented by earthy, floral undercurrents and a crisp hint of citrus in the aftertaste. This goat cheese is delightful with honey and Marcona almonds, and it also pairs beautifully with a Sauvignon Blanc.

column1: Vermont Creamery's Creamy Goat Cheese is made with fresh goats' milk coming from family farms, the milk is first pasteurized and then set overnight for natural coagulation. The next day, the fresh curd is drained and then whipped for a smooth texture. Perfect in sauces, with pasta, as a spread, or simply as a dip drizzled with maple syrup.

column1: Maasdam is a traditional, semi-hard Dutch cheese made from cow's milk. The most characteristic feature is its 'eyes' (holes) that make up most of the cheese. The cheese was created in the early 1990s as an alternative to more expensive Swiss Emmental cheese. It is a high-fat cheese with a minimum of 45% fat.

column1: Experience the authentic taste of Italy with our Calabro Cilingine Mozzarella. Handcrafted using traditional Italian methods, this small, .330z sized mozzarella cheese is a culinary gem that will transport your taste buds to the sun-drenched hills of Italy.  Made with the utmost care and attention to detail, our Calabro Cilingine Mozzarella embodies the essence of Italian craftsmanship. Crafted by skilled artisans using premium cow's milk, it captures the true flavors and textures that have made Italian mozzarella famous worldwide.  Each small piece offers a soft, milky center that melts in your mouth, releasing a burst of rich, buttery flavor. Its smooth texture and subtle tang create a delightful balance that will leave you craving more.

column1: Crumbled Gorgonzola Cheese is a delicious and versatile cheese that is perfect for adding a bold and tangy flavor to a wide range of dishes. It is made with high-quality cow's milk and has a soft and crumbly texture. This cheese has a rich and tangy flavor that is slightly salty, making it perfect for adding to salads, pasta dishes, burgers, and pizzas. It can also be used as a topping for grilled meats or added to soups and sauces to give them a rich and creamy flavor.

column1: Mini Brie cheese is a small version of the classic French soft cheese, made from cow's milk and known for its mild and creamy flavor. It is typically round in shape, with a white rind that is edible and a soft, buttery interior. Mini Brie cheese is often served as a snack or appetizer, and pairs well with crackers, bread, and fruit. It can also be melted and used in a variety of dishes, such as baked goods, quiches, and omelets.

column1: Matured, gouda-style cheese produced in the Netherlands by Cypress Groves, this cheese is made from pasteurized goat's milk and aged for six or more months to produce a dense and smooth ivory-colored paste that develops a slightly granular mouth feel as it matures off to the 12-month stage. Flavors are of lovely brown butter with intense caramel undertones. The cheese has won Gold award at World Cheese Awards 2014, Best in Class, World Championship Cheese Contest, 2010 and Best New Product in Show, NASFT Sofi Awards, 2002.

column1: Queso Fresco, a traditional Mexican cheese that is perfect for adding a creamy and slightly tangy flavor to your dishes. This exquisite cheese is made from pasteurized cow's milk, and is popular in many Latin American dishes. Queso Fresco has a crumbly and slightly moist texture, with a milky and tangy flavor that perfectly balances out the richness of your favorite dishes. It has a mild flavor that makes it perfect for pairing with a variety of other ingredients. This cheese is versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for adding to tacos, enchiladas, salads, or for using in creative dishes like queso fresco-stuffed peppers, or queso fresco-topped pizza.

column1: Stracciatella cheese is a soft and creamy Italian cheese that is made from a combination of shredded mozzarella and cream. The cheese has a delicate and tangy flavor, with a smooth and creamy texture that is perfect for spreading or spooning onto bread or crackers. Stracciatella cheese is traditionally made by hand, and is created by shredding fresh mozzarella into small pieces and mixing it with fresh cream. The resulting cheese has a lumpy and stringy texture, with a rich and creamy flavor that is perfect for use in a variety of dishes.

column1: Beemster Classic Gouda, aged 18 months, is considered the classic, Gouda throughout Holland. This traditional, authentic cheese is PDO North Holland Gouda.  The complex flavors develop as the cheese ages, naturally and slowly, on wooden planks, hand-polished and hand-turned by our master cheesemakers. Classic has a firm, yet creamy, texture dotted with crystallization throughout, a deep ochre interior and notes of toasted walnuts, caramel and a brown-butter finish. Perfection! World Cheese Awards SUPER GOLD winner.

column1: Sliced yellow cheddar cheese is a delicious and versatile cheese that is perfect for a variety of dishes. Made from high-quality cheddar cheese, this sliced cheese has a smooth texture and a rich, tangy flavor that pairs well with a variety of foods. Each slice is carefully cut to the perfect thickness, making it easy to add to sandwiches, burgers, and other dishes. It can also be used as a tasty topping for crackers or as a snack on its own.

column1: Manchego is a DOP cheese; it can be made only from the milk of the Manchega sheep that graze in the provinces of Albacete, Ciudad Real, Cuenca, and Toledo, all of which form the region of Castilla La Mancha. We have proudly sourced this Manchego for over 20 years from Quesos Corcuera, and their company spans three generations of the Corcuera family. They are based in the countryside of Toledo and are dedicated to making the best cheese possible, always producing from same day milk. Like all of their cheeses, from young to reserve, the standout characteristic of this cheese is the wonderful, well-rounded flavor of the sheep’s milk.

column1: This award-winning 26 Month XO Gouda Cheese is an authentic taste of the Netherlands long cheesemaking history. This cheese boasts strong notes of warm flavors like whiskey and butterscotch as well as sweet nuts like pecan. Aging for over two years in an a century-old warehouse allows for a crumbly yet luxuriously creamy texture that is enriched by crispy crystals. This cheese pairs beautifully with sweet flavors like honey and fig for a stunning addition to any cheese board. Each step of the production process is endowed with a human touch, from cows never treated with artificial hormones to hand-stirred curds. Beemster's production is located in Northern Holland, a region famous for its rich milk and fertile grazing land.

column1: Shredded parmesan cheese is a popular Italian-style cheese that's perfect for adding a rich and savory flavor to a wide range of dishes. This cheese is made from cow's milk and has a hard, crumbly texture that's perfect for grating or shredding. Shredded parmesan cheese has a nutty and slightly salty flavor, which makes it a popular ingredient in many Italian dishes, including pasta dishes, salads, and pizzas. It's also a great addition to soups, stews, and casseroles, as well as a variety of other recipes.

column1: Halloumi cheese is a traditional Cypriot cheese made from a mixture of sheep and goat's milk (sometimes cow's milk is also used). It has a firm, dense, and slightly rubbery texture, and a mild, salty taste. Halloumi cheese can be eaten fresh or grilled, and is often used as a meat substitute in vegetarian dishes. It is a popular ingredient in Mediterranean cuisine and is also commonly used in salads, sandwiches, and as a topping for pizza.

column1: This Gorgonzola Cheese Wheel boats a solid yet crumbly texture and an invigorating salty, earthy flavor. Handcrafted with only the freshest rBST-free milk from local farms, this cheese undergoes a 90-day cave aging process during which the wheels are punctured so that air can circulate and encourage gorgonzola’s characteristic blue mold to develop. This award-winning cheese pairs beautifully with figs, pears, and walnuts for a stunning spread.

column1: Semolina flour is a type of flour that is made from durum wheat, a hard wheat that is high in protein and gluten. The flour has a coarse texture and a pale yellow color, and is often used in Italian and Middle Eastern cuisines. Semolina flour is most commonly used to make pasta, bread, and pizza dough. Its high gluten content gives these products a chewy and satisfying texture, and its coarse texture helps the dough to hold its shape during the cooking process.

column1: Fontina is believed to have originated in Valle d'Aosta, Italy high in the Alps near the borders of France and Switzerland. Since this geographic area has been in constant fluctuation, little recorded history exists on the exact origin of this marvelous cheese. However, in 1951 at the Stresa Convention, it was declared that Fontina made in Valle d'Aosta, Italy with unpasteurized milk was the original. Those cheeses made with pasteurized milk on an industrial scale should actually be called Fontal

column1: This 60% Brie Cheese Wheel is the luxuriously creamy key to any cheese lover’s heart. Made from pasteurized cow’s milk in northeastern France, this cheese boasts a thin white rind and a silky smooth interior. With a robust buttery flavor complemented by undercurrents of hazelnut and mushroom, this cheese is best enjoyed at room temperature. Try on a cheese board with honey and pear or toss into a delectable bite-sized tartlet with caramelized onions.

column1: 100% pure sheep's milk cheese produced in France's Basque region in the Pyrenees Mountains, the region that spans the border between France and Spain, traditionally, it was handmade by shepherds from left over curds set aside from milking their ewes. Even today Petit Basque is made using the same methods applied by the local shepherds. The semi-hard cheese is aged for a minimum of 70 days, during which it develops a basket-weave pattern similar to Spain's famous Manchego cheese but with milder and delicate favor. It has a distinctive aroma of sheep's milk, and a smooth, sweet flavor with a nutty finish.

column1: Shredded jack cheese is a type of cheese that has been pre-shredded into small pieces. It is made from pasteurized cow's milk and has a mild, buttery flavor with a slightly tangy finish. The cheese is soft and creamy, making it a great addition to a variety of dishes such as tacos, nachos, salads, and sandwiches. Shredded jack cheese is a popular ingredient in many Mexican and Tex-Mex dishes, and it can be used as a topping for pizzas and casseroles.

column1: New School is a Premium American Cheese done right!  Made with aged cheddar, real cream, and real butter, we only use the best ingredients and a simple process. No oils, starches, phosphates, artificial colors, or synthetic taste. Co-founded by Iron Chef winner and Food Network regular Chef Eric Greenspan, this is finally a premium American cheese that you can serve proudly without compromise, from a brand you can trust. New School delivers the creamy, melty, comforting qualities you expect from American cheese with even better taste and unrivaled quality. Great for burgers, grilled cheese, breakfast sandwiches, cheesesteaks, mac & cheese, and any other dish that needs an ooey gooey delicious melting cheese.

column1: An organic American Original cheese recipe, our best-selling cheese has all the lusciousness you expect from a triple cream with a unique heart that upholds its texture. column1: A gluten-free semi-hard, Dutch style, farmer's cheese made from pasteurized cow's milk, produced by Point Reyes Farmstead Cheese Company, California, US, this cheese made with microbial rennet has a buttery, creamy flavor with a grassy tang finish. Toma is wonderful on a cheese board or with omelets, burgers, sauces. Try pairing it with Hop-heavy beers, Pinot noir, Scotch. The cheese has won many awards including silver medal at 2010 World Cheese Awards in London, gold medal at 2011 California State Fair, 1st place ribbon in 2011 American Cheese Society in Montreal.

column1: Parmesan cheese, as it is called in English, is considered to be among the top cheeses by cheese connoisseurs. Today, it is produced by various producers. However, PDO designation states that for a cheese to be called as Parmesan, it has to be produced from cows grazing on fresh grass and hay. Cheeses mocking Parmigiano Reggiano are called as Parmesan or Italian hard cheese by producers to avoid legal issues. Parmigiano Reggiano cheese is named after the provinces in which it is made, namely Provinces of Parma, Reggio Emilia, Modena, Bologna and Mantua. True Parmesan cheese has a hard, gritty texture and is fruity and nutty in taste.

column1: Made from 100% raw cow's milk in the regions of Reggio-Emilia, Modena and Parma, Parmigiano Reggiano is quite possibly Italy's most famous cheese. Mitica® Parmigiano Reggiano is sourced from a premium family of carefully selected farms. Farms are selected based on quality, artistry, location, and flavor profile. All wheels are aged a minimum of 24 months and receive extra testing during aging, receiving the coveted Export stamp by the Consorzio to further ensure the quality. Parmigiano Reggiano is an iconic cheese and when you choose Mitica®, you are choosing the best in class.

column1: A semi-hard cheese made on both sides of the French and Swiss Alps, Valais Raclette or Fromage a Raclette, as they are traditionally called, are made using ancestral methods with unpasteurized milk of cows grazing on the alpine meadows. The name Raclette comes from the French word �racler�, which means �to scrape�. The cheese has got a thin, brownish-orange colored rind and a pale-yellow pate with a few and scattered open holes. It is having a very distinctive pleasant, aromatic smell with a creamy texture, similar to Gruyere cheeses, which does not separate even when melted. The flavor can vary from nutty, slightly acidic to milky.

column1: Belgioioso Platinum Shredded Mozzarella Cheese, a premium quality cheese that is perfect for adding a rich and creamy flavor to your dishes. This exquisite cheese is made with the freshest milk from cows that are free from artificial hormones and antibiotics, ensuring a pure and natural taste. Belgioioso Platinum Shredded Mozzarella Cheese has a beautiful white color and a fresh aroma of milk. It has a soft and creamy texture that melts easily, creating a delicious and satisfying flavor that is perfect for pizzas, lasagnas, or any dish that requires a rich and smooth cheese. This shredded mozzarella cheese is versatile and can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for adding to salads, sandwiches, or for using in creative dishes like stuffed chicken or baked ziti.

column1: Lupara frozen bufala mozzarella is a premium quality Italian cheese made from the milk of water buffaloes. The cheese is known for its delicate, milky flavor and soft, creamy texture. Lupara bufala mozzarella is made using traditional techniques and is frozen to preserve its freshness and flavor. It can be used in a variety of recipes, such as pizzas, salads, sandwiches, and pasta dishes.

column1: For nine long months, we wait. That's what it takes to produce the full-bodied, naturally-aged sharpness of Tillamook Sharp Cheddar. For our farmer-owners, patience isn't just a virtue, it's a value, and it guides the cheesemaking process. Maybe that's why the United States Championship Cheese Contest voted it'America's Best'. We think you'll agree when you use it to zing up your appetizers, main dishes, and sandwiches.

column1: This Red Wax Gouda Cheese brings the rich flavors of the Dutch cheesemaking tradition to your own plate. This pressed, uncooked cheese is crafted from cow’s milk for a decadently creamy and semi-soft texture. This gouda is left to mature for a minimum of 30 days before undergoing a classic hickory cold smoking process that results in a gorgeous honey-colored rind. Aging for another 30 days after smoking results in a toasty, buttery flavor with notes of caramel that perfectly complement the smoky undertone. Enjoy with a chilled glass of Riesling or Gernache for a delightful after-dinner treat, or pair with stone fruits like apricots and cherries.

With a creamy texture and a rich buttery tang, cheddar lovers are known to pair it with sweet and tart fruits like apples and pears, melt it into sauces and dips, or make it the centerpiece of an epic cheese and crackers platter.

column1: Grated Romano cheese is a hard, salty Italian cheese that is a popular alternative to the more widely-known Parmesan cheese. It is made from sheep's milk and aged for at least five months to develop its distinctive flavor and texture. Grated Romano cheese is typically sold in small containers and is ready to use right out of the package. It has a sharp, tangy taste that adds depth and complexity to a wide range of dishes, including pasta, salads, soups, and pizzas.

column1: Using a century's old method from Britain this cheddar is wrapped in cheesecloth and cave-aged for 6-8 months. Aging in cloth allows this cheese to take on a deeper variety of flavors than its plastic-aged counterparts, and at a younger age. The texture is firm and creamy with a tendency to crumble. Clothbound Cheddar has a mottled gray rind with aromas of cave, mushrooms, and fresh butter. Flavors are similar to a traditional English cheddar: grassy, nutty notes dominate with some lemony accents and a smooth, lactic body that carries on through a meaty finish.

column1: Royal Mahout Paneer Indian style cheese. Does not melt when cooked. Use in your favorite Indian style dishes that call for paneer � saag paneer, tiki masala etc. Traditionally a homemade cheese, Paneer is similar to pressed Ricotta, except the curd is drier and has no salt added. Paneer is among the primary protein sources for hindus and buddhists who adhere to strict vegetarian (no animal rennet) diets. Paneer is popular in curried dishes, and can also be wrapped in dough and fried. Since this cheese does not melt, it can also be used in preparation of popular desserts because of its delightful texture. Paneer can be frozen to extend its shelf life indefinitely, although the freezing may make the texture more crumbly.

column1: This 12-month Comte is an undeniable French favorite. With a bold, nutty flavor roughly similar to parmigiano reggiano and a firm yet delightfully creamy texture, this cheese is aged in the revered Fort des Rousses cellar. Expert cheesemakers oversee the aging process to ensure that only the finest cheeses make their way to your plate. Comte pairs wonderfully with hints of sweetness like candied nuts or fruity white wines.

column1: Calabro mozzarella is a type of fresh, soft cheese that is known for its mild, milky flavor and smooth, creamy texture. It is made from cow's milk and is a popular ingredient in many types of cuisine, particularly Italian and Mediterranean dishes. Calabro mozzarella is typically sold in ball-shaped form, and is made using traditional cheese-making methods. The cheese is stretched and kneaded by hand to create its distinctive texture and flavor, and is then immersed in brine to enhance its flavor and texture.

column1: Burrata is an ultra soft cheese made from cow's milk. This cheese is made from fresh heavy cream and unspun mozzarella curds. The combined ingredients are placed into the center of a thin skin made from fresh mozzarella that is formed into a round shape, similar to a cloth bag. It has a rich, silky texture and the flavor is at once sweet and earthy with a slightly sour, yogurty backbone, as well as elusive hints of flowers and grass that linger on the palate.

column1: Produced on a family farm since 2000, California’s classic style blue cheese is rindless, all-natural and gluten-free. The Giacomini Family, third generation dairy farmers in West Marin, CA, have been making farmstead products  since 1959. They converted their milk into cheese in 2000 and introduced Original Blue’. The flavor of their crumbled blue is bold with hints of sweet milk and a peppery finish. This cheese is made from raw (non-pasteurized), rBST-free cows’ milk, microbial (vegetarian) rennet and aged for 3.5 months.

column1: This world-famous Roquefort is a noble, all-natural ewe's milk blue cheese from the Auvergne region of France. Papillon (which means butterfly in French) wraps their top-of-the-line Roquefort in black foil to distinguish it from lesser brands. Aged for over 4 months in the natural Combalou Caves, this exceptional Papillon Roquefort is distinguished first and foremost by its white curd and the intense blue which generously marbles its wide and numerous cavities. The taste of a good Roquefort is similar, in terms of analysis, to a grand cru wine: balanced and fairly salty, with a big personality. It is great for melting, slightly granulated, and lingers in the mouth. In the mouth, its unctuous and supple texture melts deliciously with a recognizable taste, and leaves you with a powerful and lingering aftertaste.

column1: Also called "Boule de Lille", this cheese dates to the reign of Louis XIV, who prohibited the import of Dutch cheeses into France. The residents of Flanders (now part of Belgium), the northernmost region of France, had strong cultural ties to Holland (many still speak Dutch as their first language today) and dearly loved the banished Dutch specialties. Their alternatives were to either smuggle in the contraband cheeses or make a go at producing their own - with a French twist, of course! And so, Mimolette was born. Aged Mimolette is a semi-hard cheese that has the same texture and spherical shape as Dutch Edam, but with a natural rind. It is produced in bowling-ball shaped 7-pound spheres with a bright, orange-colored interior. Because of its hue, it is sometimes called the "Halloween Cheese.

column1: Locatelli is a brand of Pecorino Romano cheese, a type of Italian cheese made from sheep's milk. It has a salty, sharp flavor and a hard, granular texture that is suitable for grating. Locatelli Pecorino Romano is often used as a grating cheese in pasta dishes, soups, and salads, and is a popular ingredient in Italian cuisine. column1: Philadelphia Original Cream Cheese traces its roots back to 1872, and it has been the standard of high quality cream cheese ever since. Today, it is made with five simple ingredients and is perfect for adding creaminess to recipes. You already love it for cheesecakes and dips, but be sure to give it a try for making creamy pasta sauce, delectable no-bake desserts, rich soups and much more. Local dairy farmers near Beaver Dam, WI and Lowville, NY supply Philly with fresh milk, which we combine with real cream. The entire process from farm to creamery takes just six days. But we don't stop at farm fresh milk and real cream. We also never add artificial preservatives, flavors or dyes in any of our cream cheese spreads. So in the end, everything just seems a little bit better with the creamy taste of Philly.

column1: The term “ricotta,” Italian for “recooked” refers to the twice-heated curd that originally developed as a way to conserve the whey left over in the cheesemaking process. Recooking gives Calabro Fresh Ricotta a distinctive curdy texture and sweet, creamy flavor. Made using traditional techniques, this authentic Italian cheese is bright and milky, making it ideal for baking into lasagna or cheesecakes.

column1: A pasteurized cow's milk, soft-ripened French cheese that is in the double-crème category. Mild and buttery, it is an amazing addition to the Brie world. It is produced from milk that has been specially filtered to break down some of the fat content, yielding a lighter, smoother, silkier texture than other Brie. The filtering makes the Fromage d’Affinois lighter than other Brie in terms of weight but is certainly creamier and a little thicker than most. The cheese is made using a process known as ultra-filtration. The process is somewhat similar to homogenization and serves to remove water from the milk. This concentrate and distributes all the other components in the milk, including fat, evenly throughout the paste. Ultra-filtration imparts a taste as rich as most triple-cremes, although the fat content is closer to a double-creme. In addition to retaining more fat, ultrafiltration allows the cheese to retain more protein and nutrients, and accelerates the cheese making process. Whereas Brie takes eight weeks to make, Fromage d'Affinois takes just two. When ripe the cheese has a runny texture that coats like icing. The rind is flawless and adds flavor to the sweetness of the cheese.

column1: Kilchurn Estate  Krystal Pure Cave Aged Cheddar is made using pasteurized cow's milk and the same culture that is used in Parmigiano Reggiano, to produce calcium crystals. After aging in caves in Southern England for 15 months, the end result is one of our sharpest cheddars and a creamy texture peppered with calcium crystals. The unique qualities of this exceptional cheddar are best for showcasing on a cheeseboard with sweet apricot preserves and a glass of port or a pale ale.

column1: A long, gentle cold-smoking over local hazelnut shells infuses Rogue Creamery's Smokey Blue cheese with an added layer of rich flavor and terroir. Sweet cream flavors and caramel notes balance earthy flavors of smoke and hints of roasted nuts. The result is a cakey yet smooth blue cheese reminiscent of candied bacon. Sweet, nutty, savory flavors envelope the rich milk creating a hint of the toasted, sweet richness of a campfire. Pairs perfectly with ale.

column1: Named after the company's co-owner, Nancy's Camembert is a meltingly creamy, soft ripened cheese, made from a blend of sheep's milk, cow's milk, and cow's cream. When young, the texture is semi-soft in the center of the cheese, becoming smoother and softer just under the rind. The rind can be quite dense and slightly chewy. As the cheese matures, the texture becomes quite runny under the rind, while the center retains its cohesiveness

column1: For a cheese as sophisticated as it is flavorful, try this sottocenere flavored with truffle. Pasteurized cow’s milk adds a delightfully creamy texture to this semi-soft cheese, while an infusion of truffles adds a rich earthy flavor with notes of mushroom. Sweet spices like cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves bring a sense of warmth and create a speckled pattern on the interior, while licorice, fennel and coriander add further complexity to its earthy profile. Maturing in beech ash contributes a woody aroma leaves the rind a pale brownish gray sure to stand out on any cheese board.

column1: Fontina is believed to have originated in Valle d'Aosta, Italy high in the Alps near the borders of France and Switzerland. Since this geographic area has been in constant fluctuation, little recorded history exists on the exact origin of this marvelous cheese. However, in 1951 at the Stresa Convention, it was declared that Fontina made in Valle d'Aosta, Italy with unpasteurized milk was the original. Those cheeses made with pasteurized milk on an industrial scale should actually be called Fontal

column1: This Compagnie Fromage Triple Creme Cheese is the manifestation of a rich cheesemaking tradition from the Normandy region of France’s northwestern quadrant. Heavy cream is added to the cheese for a roughly 75% fat composition, rendering this option the height of cheesy decadence. With a bloomy white rind and a delicately soft, spreadable texture, this cheese is reminiscent of a classic French brie. Enjoy with savory or sweet pairings for a perfect amuse-bouche. Try with a fresh baguette, walnuts, and a drizzle of maple syrup for an autumn-inspired appetizer, or pair with ice wine for a perfect balance of richness and sweetness.

column1: This is the perfect combination of classic Toma paired with the aromatic flavors of Italian Black Truffles from Umbria.  Reminiscent of undergrowth, fresh strawberries, dried fruit and a hint of cocoa, the earthy flavor marries beautifully with the buttery richness of Toma. Made from pasteurized, rBST-free cows’ milk, microbial (vegetarian) rennet, gluten free and aged for 90 days.

column1: Buf burrata has an outer mozzarella cheese encasing a creamy interior of cows milk and water buffalo cream. Hand tied with our signature knot. Sprinkle with a little salt and olive oil and spread it on bread, crackers, or in caprese! Water buffalo milk is not only creamy and delicious, at BUF they go the extra mile to create a product that’s uniquely theirs. You can definitely taste the difference! The only non-GMO certified creamery in the world, they are proud leaders in responsibly produced water buffalo products. Through their trademark cheese making process, they have created a line of products that are lactose free, 100% vegetarian rennet, and rich in omega-3s. All our milk is A2.

BelGioioso Fontina makes an excellent introduction to Italian cheeses "€ everyone likes Fontina. This versatile cheese makes delicious sandwiches and grilled cheese and melts easily for fondues and sauces.

column1: This award-winning Truffle Tremor Goat Cheese elegantly combines two of the finer things in life. This cheese begins in Humboldt Count, California, with fresh goat milk from Cypress Grove’s American Humane Certified dairy. Rich truffles add a full-bodied earthy flavor with mushroomy and floral nuances. Soft-ripened with an immaculate white bloomy rind, this cheese has an exquisitely soft, delicate texture. Pair with fruity whites like Gerwüztraminer or Moscato for a dose of indulgence at any time of day.

column1: Gorgonzola Dolce is a type of Italian blue cheese that is known for its rich, creamy texture and sweet, mild flavor. It is made from cow's milk and is aged for a short period of time, which results in a softer and milder flavor compared to other blue cheeses. Gorgonzola Dolce is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of culinary applications. It is often crumbled and used as a topping for salads and pizzas, or served on a cheese platter with other types of cheese and accompaniments. It can also be used in sauces, dressings, and dips, or melted into a risotto or pasta dish.

column1: Calabro mozzarella is a type of fresh, soft cheese that is known for its mild, milky flavor and smooth, creamy texture. It is made from cow's milk and is a popular ingredient in many types of cuisine, particularly Italian and Mediterranean dishes. Calabro mozzarella is typically sold in ball-shaped form, and is made using traditional cheese-making methods. The cheese is stretched and kneaded by hand to create its distinctive texture and flavor, and is then immersed in brine to enhance its flavor and texture.

column1: Philadelphia Original Cream Cheese traces its roots back to 1872, and it has been the standard of high quality cream cheese ever since. Today, it is made with five simple ingredients and is perfect for adding creaminess to recipes. You already love it for cheesecakes and dips, but be sure to give it a try for making creamy pasta sauce, delectable no-bake desserts, rich soups and much more. Local dairy farmers near Beaver Dam, WI and Lowville, NY supply Philly with fresh milk, which we combine with real cream. The entire process from farm to creamery takes just six days. But we don't stop at farm fresh milk and real cream. We also never add artificial preservatives, flavors or dyes in any of our cream cheese spreads. So in the end, everything just seems a little bit better with the creamy taste of Philly.

column1: The perfect cheese to eat with fruit. Creamy with an open texture, Wensleydale is one of the oldest cheese varieties in England as monks were first known to be making Wensleydale in the 11th century. Wensleydale has a natural sweet acidity that complements fruit, best of all cranberries. Savile Row uses plump cranberries and add them to the cheese creating a great, sweet, and juicy cheese.

column1: Chihuahua cheese, also known as queso blanco, is a type of Mexican cheese that's known for its mild flavor and creamy texture. This cheese is a popular ingredient in many Mexican dishes, including quesadillas, enchiladas, and chiles rellenos. Chihuahua cheese is a soft and moist cheese that's made from cow's milk. It has a smooth and slightly elastic texture that makes it perfect for melting and blending with other ingredients. It has a delicate and mild flavor that's slightly tangy and slightly sweet, making it a versatile ingredient in many recipes.

column1: This low-moisture Whole Milk Mozzarella Cheese Loaf brings a generous dose of refined Italian tradition to any pizza, salad, or creamy pasta dish. Crafted with farm-fresh whole milk from rBST-free cows and only all-natural ingredients, this mozzarella has a firm texture and a moderately creamy, slightly salty savory flavor. Natural fermentation adds a host of delightful buttery notes. This whole milk variety boasts a beautifully even melt when heated, making it an ideal companion for quiches, lasagnas, paninis, and pizzas.

column1: For an authentic bite of New England’s rolling pastures, this Smoked Vermont Cheddar Cheese is a quintessential addition to any cheese board. Handcrafted using rBST-free milk from family farms across Vermont, this cheese is cold-smoked with maple wood for a delightfully earthy, smoky flavor. With a rich, velvety texture and just a slight undertone of sweetness, this cheese is a perfect pairing for full-bodied red wines like Syrah as well as dry ciders.

column1: is a matured, gouda-style cheese produced in the Netherlands and sold under the Cypress Grove Chevre label. Made from pasteurized sheep's milk, the cheese is aged for 3-6 months to produce a paste that is deep buttery in color with a smooth firm texture. Flavors are sweet and buttery at initial stage of ripening but develop an incredible sweetness of caramels and nutty undertones as it fully matures.

column1: The ivory-colored Montchevre® Bucheron® Cheese is well known for offering the taste and texture of two cheeses in one. This cheese usually matures for 5-10 weeks, resulting in a dense center and gooey cream line rich in flavor with discreet earthy undertones; truly a delectable blend filled with the flavors of Montchevre® cheese high quality fresh goat's milk. The beautiful rind on the Montchevre® Bucheron® Cheese makes it the perfect centerpiece for a cheese board; however, it is also delicious melted into a quiche, on a crostini or on your favorite steak.

column1: Whole milk ricotta is made by heating the whey until the proteins coagulate, then draining and pressing the resulting curds. The cheese is then blended with whole milk, which gives it a creamy texture and rich flavor. It has a slightly sweet taste and a smooth, velvety texture that is perfect for spreading on bread or crackers or for use in recipes. Whole Milk Ricotta cheese is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of dishes, both savory and sweet. It is commonly used in Italian cooking, such as in lasagna, stuffed shells, and cannoli. It can also be used in dips, spreads, and sauces, and makes a delicious addition to pancakes or waffles.

column1:
Exclusively made for Chefs Warehouse, Savile Row Irish pub cheddar is aged over 12 Months, made from the milk of grass fed cows. This cheese has a wonderful sweet caramelized flavor that melts in the mouth and leaves 
you wanting more. It’s the perfect pub cheese to pair with a frosty ale. Ireland is world-famous for its cheese making and this all links back to Ireland having the perfect climate to grow rich green grass for the cows to graze on freely. Good cheese comes from good animal husbandry
and good grass, and Ireland offers this in abundance.

column1: This Bocconcini Mozzarella Cheese brings a generous dose of Italian tradition to any salad or pre-dinner amuse-bouche. Crafted with farm-fresh whole milk from rBST-free cows, this mozzarella has a soft, light texture and a creamy, slightly sweet flavor. Its name comes from the Italian for “mouth,” demonstrating its bite-size that falls larger than ciliegine but more petite than ovolini. Use as the centerpiece of a refreshing summer caprese salad or try deep fried with flour, egg, and breadcrumbs for a crispy crowd-pleaser.

column1:
Stella® Blue Cheese features the trademark attributes that true blue cheese lovers seek: a delectably rich and tangy flavor and an easy-to-crumble, semi-soft texture that’s perfect for salads and sauces.

Stella® Blue Cheese’s impactful flavor also shines in dips and spreads. Take Buffalo wings from ho-hum to fabulous: simply melt Stella® Blue Cheese as a hearty dip. Add an extra layer of flavor to your grilled meats by sprinkling blue cheese crumbles on burgers and steaks. Or combine Stella® Blue Cheese crumbles with a dash of bourbon and add to your favorite bottled BBQ sauce for a tangy taste infusion. With Stella® Blue Cheese, the possibilities are endless!

column1: This is a French triple creme cow's milk cheese with a powdery white, bloomy skin of mold. Originally developed and manufactured by the Soulie cheese factory in Villefranche-de-Rouergue, Aveyron, it is now produced in Vire, Calvados. It has a soft buttery texture, tangy edible rind, and tastes like an intense version of Brie.

column1: A yellow, medium-hard cheese that originated in the area around Emmental, in Switzerland with the classic large eye structure we associate with "Swiss Cheese." In cooking, it is often put on top of gratins, or dishes which are put in the oven to let the cheese melt and become golden-brown and crusty. It is also used for fondue, in which case it is mixed with Gruyere cheese.

column1: Monterey Jack melts easily and has a buttery taste to it. Soft, white, and mild this cheese is gentle on the palate with just a hint of acidity. Monterey Jack is the perfect accompaniment to many dishes and is especially great with mexican inspired favorites like tacos, nachos, dips, and fajitas.

column1: For the first time in the 1970s, it was made by Andy Williamson at the Castle Stuart dairy in Inverness and therefore  it was called Blue Stuart or 'Inverness-shire Blue'. It is a semi-firm blue cheese described as a cross between Stilton and Cheshire. In a period of 10-12 weeks, it forms an orange-brown, natural rind and smooth texture. With a sharp, strong flavor and a bit tangy aroma, it is a vegetarian's cheese having a fat content of 48%.

column1: This Old-Fashioned Mozzarella Cheese Loaf brings a generous dose of refined Italian tradition to any pizza, salad, or creamy pasta dish. Crafted with farm-fresh whole milk from rBST-free cows, this mozzarella has a soft, light texture and a creamy, slightly sweet flavor. This old-fashioned variety boasts a buttery light yellow color as opposed to the milky white of fresh mozzarella. Use in an inspired ciabatta grilled cheese with pesto and tomato or grate over stuffed peppers for a satisfying, flavorful entree.

column1:
Quality milk, cave aging and old-world technique. This cave aged cheddar is hand 
selected by Jasper Hill Farm for the Chefs’ Warehouse. Unique to this production 
of cheddar is the addition of Alpine cultures, resulting in a sweet and nutty in 
flavor. The texture is pliable and meltable, making it ideal to perform in recipes. A
stunner on the cheese board paired with marmalade or pickled vegetables.

column1: The Salzarulo family is behind the Lioni name and began its latticini tradition in over 100 years ago in the town of Lioni, Italy which is in Campania. The family moved the business to Brooklyn in 1980, building its reputation upon its fresh, whole milk mozzarella. Their products contain no additives or preservatives and are made from the freshest whole cows milk. This one pound mozzarella ball is delicately smoked over all-natural hardwood smoke chips on the premises. It is slightly moist to the touch and low-moisture, perfect for melting in pan of baked macaroni, on pizza, in risotto with chanterelle mushrooms or slicing for sandwiches.

column1: This 24-Month Parmesan Reggiano Cheese Wheel is edible proof that good things really do take time. This PDO cheese is crafted using cow’s milk from particular Italian regions including Parma and Bologna, allowing for a taste of tradition that is difficult to top. Aging yields an unmistakeable sensation of umami and a robust nutty, vaguely fruity flavor. This cheese is lactose free and offers a hard, dense texture perfect for an indulgent snack or simple garnish. Pair with a glass of chilled Chianti or Sauvignon Blanc for a delightful after-dinner treat.

column1: A Jasper Hill Farm original that is made from our high-quality whole raw milk, it is named for an old military road commissioned by George Washington during the Revolutionary War. Though no major battle ever took place, the road brought Greensboro its first settlers and continues to be used today. Bayley has developed a loyal following because of its fudge-like texture, toasted-nut sweetness, and anise spice character. The paste is dense and creamy, with well-distributed blue veins. The usual peppery character of blue cheese is subdued, giving way to the grassy, nutty flavors in the milk.

column1: This Cana De Oveja Sheep Milk Cheese begins with pasteurized sheep’s milk from the grassy pastures of Spain’s Murcia region. Soft-ripened for a lusciously creamy interior and a firm bloomy rind with a touch of sharpness, this cheese is roughly reminiscent of France’s Bucheron variety. Aging for 21 days creates a wonderfully buttery flavor with just a hint of acidity, perfect for enjoying with sweet white wines and dried fruit.

column1: Described as a mixture between Cheddar and Parmigiano Reggiano, Dubliner tastes of a mature Cheddar with the sweet aftertaste of Reggiano. Created by the Irish company Kerrygold and named after Ireland's capital city, this cheese shares traits with several well-known cheeses, but the combination creates a flavor that is completely unique. This cheese is made from pasteurized cow's milk. All Kerrygold products are made using microbial rennet, making them suitable for vegetarians. Irish Dubliner Cheese is a robust aged cow's milk cheese with somewhat of a hard texture like cheddar. In one bite of Irish Dubliner, you can taste the different flavors of nutty, sharp, and sweet - which can only come from a natural cheese made from the milk of grass-fed cows.

column1: Bar Valley Foods Cheddar Cheese Sauce is a delicious and versatile sauce perfect for enhancing the flavor of your favorite dishes. column1: Fresh Lasagna Pasta Sheets are a type of Italian pasta that is used to make the classic Italian dish, lasagna. They are made from a blend of durum wheat semolina and fresh eggs, and have a delicate texture and a rich, savory flavor. The pasta sheets are cut into large, rectangular shapes, and are perfect for layering in a lasagna dish. They are also versatile and can be used in a wide range of other pasta dishes, such as cannelloni or baked ziti.

column1: Daiya Vegan Shredded Cheddar is a dairy-free, plant-based alternative to traditional shredded cheddar cheese. It is made from cassava and arrowroot flours, and features a creamy, tangy, and cheesy flavor that is ideal for topping or melting on all sorts of dishes such as pizza, tacos, and casseroles. It is also free from common allergens, including dairy, soy, and gluten, making it a great choice for those with dietary restrictions.

column1: Pecorino Romano is a type of hard cheese that is made from sheep's milk. It is a traditional Italian cheese that is known for its salty, nutty, and tangy flavor, and is often used as a seasoning in many Italian dishes.  Pecorino Romano is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of culinary applications. It is often grated and used as a topping for pasta dishes, salads, and soups, or served on a cheese platter with other types of cheese and accompaniments. It can also be used as a seasoning in sauces, dressings, and marinades.

column1:
Originally from the town of Cotija in Michoacan, Mexico, this firm, full flavored, bold cheese is becoming more popular by the minute in the U.S. Sometimes called the “parmesan of Mexico”, Cotija cheese can be shaken over any dish for an unparalleled flavor boost. We craft our unique Cotija cheese with whole milk and no processed ingredients, resulting in the traditional bold flavor with rich dairy notes.

All of our products are made in the United States.

column1: Nettle Meadow's most famous cheese is made from a blend of pasteurized farmstead goat's milk and cow's milk cream. Kunik, the Inuit term for an Eskimo kiss, has a bloomy rind, and which the edges of the triple creme paste ripens evenly, while the center remains dense and acidified. Kunik most recently won two gold medals at the World Cheese Championships as well as at the American Cheese Society 2016 Awards.

column1: In Tuscany, an ancient harmony is recognized between the flavor of pecorino and the bouquet of wine. This harmony is played out beautifully in Brillo Pecorino DiVino, which is made from pure sheep's milk and seasoned with wine. Pecorino is one of the most ancient cheeses in the world and can be traced back nearly 2,000 years to a time when sheepherding was still the principle means of livelihood for the people of Italy. Wine's history is even longer, so bringing these two culinary ancients together was a natural combination. The burgundy-colored crust of brillo is edible, but the wine treatment lends a distinctive flavor to the interior as well.

column1: Named for a philanthropic dairy farmer who built the Greensboro library in 1900, Alpha's grandfather, Enoch, was one of our town's original settlers. His namesake cheese is made in our satellite creamery, located within the Vermont Food Venture Center in Hardwick, VT - a facility designed to incubate value-added projects and enrich our agricultural economy. This cheese is like Alpine cheeses like Appenzeller, which inspired the recipe for this Jasper Hill Creamery original. Alpha Tolman has a buttery, fruit & nut flavor when young, developing bold meaty, caramelized onion flavors as it matures. The texture is dense and pliant, easily portioned, and ideal for melting.

column1: Buf Ovoline Mozzarella's round shape and pristine white appearance adds a touch of visual elegance to any dish. BUF goes the extra mile to create a product that’s uniquely theirs. You can definitely taste the difference! The only non-GMO certified creamery in the world, they are proud leaders in responsibly produced water buffalo products. Through their trademark cheese making process, they have created a line of products that are lactose free, 100% vegetarian rennet, and rich in omega-3s. All their milk is A2. Buf Creamery Ovoline Mozzarella captures the essence of Italy's most celebrated cheese. It boasts a delicate, milky flavor with a subtle tang, creating a perfect balance that is sure to delight the most discerning palates.

column1: In 1899, Giuseppe Pollio left his native Italy for the promise of America. Bringing his family's special talent for cheese-making, Giuseppe started the Polly-O cheese company in a small Brooklyn store front with a simple promise: to make the finest cheeses by using only the freshest ingredients. More than a century later, we're proud to uphold the Pollio family promise by offering only the very best to you and your family.

column1: Burrata is an ultra soft cheese made from cow's milk. This cheese is made from fresh heavy cream and unspun mozzarella curds. The combined ingredients are placed into the center of a thin skin made from fresh mozzarella that is formed into a round shape, similar to a cloth bag. It has a rich, silky texture and the flavor is at once sweet and earthy with a slightly sour, yogurty backbone, as well as elusive hints of flowers and grass that linger on the palate.

column1: A hard cheese, similar to a more typical Cheddar but much more moist and crumblier with a milder flavor. It matures faster than cheddar and can be sold as young as two months. A good Leicester cheese can be identified by a firm body and a close, flaky texture. Though the cheese can be consumed young, to reach its optimum flavor, it should be allowed to mature for six to nine months. A good cheese tastes slightly sweet with an almost caramel flavor and builds up a more robust taste as its ages.

column1: An exclusive Jasper Hill Farm creation, a creamery that not only makes cheeses but also offers cheese maturing caves for other Vermont based producers, the cheese was originally created by Marisa Mauro's Ploughgate Creamery, but after a fire in 2011, Jaspers resurrected the recipe and continue to make it at their farm. This washed-rind cheese is made from pasteurized cow's milk. It has a semi-soft, buttery texture with occasional eyes and pale yellow-caramel paste. Flavors range from delicate milky, herbal, ripe-peach that advance into peat, roasted beef and onions aromas imparted by the rind.

column1: This award-winning fresh mozzarella cheese boasts an exquisitely rich flavor alongside a delicate, silky texture. This mozzarella begins with rBST-free cows’s milk, which is collected from local farms within hours of milking for ultimate freshness. This cheese comes packed in convenient 10-ounce balls, making it an effortless addition to paninis, wraps, pizzas, and lasagnas. Enjoy with fire-roasted red peppers, fresh basil, and balsamic glaze for a simple salad that is sure to please.

column1: A Jasper Hill Creamery cheese named after Anne Harbison, the original contributor to the making of this cheese, it is a soft-ripened cow's milk cheese with a bloomy rind, wrapped in strips of spruce cambium, which are harvested from the woodlands of Jasper Hill.  When ripe, Harbison has a very spoon able texture that continues to soften until consumed. It’s woodsy and sweet with lemony, mustardy, and vegetal flavors. Oaked white wine or barrel-aged sour beers make great accompaniments. The cheese is held together by the bark, which can be peeled off when it is a bit younger. However, with loosened cheese, it is better that the bark is kept as is and the portions are spooned out separately.

column1: Light, ultra-creamy, and easily spreadable, this Philadelphia cream cheese spread makes it easy to adorn bagels, toast, and sandwiches with a timeless, popular topping. Made using only simple ingredients, this cream cheese provides a fresh and tangy flavor and exceptional spreadability! For the ultimate convenience, it is packaged in bulk 3 lb. tubs, allowing you to choose the perfect serving size for your establishment without the increased cost of purchasing cream cheese pre-portioned into individual cups. This rich cream cheese spread is soft and ready to use, making it easy to slather on bagels or other delicious baked goods to maintain speedy service at your high-traffic restaurant!

column1: Ultra-rich Italian cream cheese, Mascarpone is fresh and mild with a delicate sweet cream flavor. Italian mascarpone is made from cream gathered from cows grazing on grasses, herbs and flowers in Lombardy. Italian Mascarpone is much richer than American-style cream cheese, and is made without starters or rennet. While nearly everyone associates mascarpone with the dessert classic tiramisu, it can also be layered between fresh berries and zabaglione, or served with fresh figs. Mascarpone is versatile for savory dishes, too, in place of butter or heavy cream to enrich a cream sauce, or for risotto.

column1: Topped with CA Bay Laurel leaves, it is a soft-ripened, bloomy rind cheese, inspired by the very famous, seasonally-made Vacherin Mont d’Or and its close variation L’Edel de Cléron, both from the Jura mountain region along the French-Swiss border. Quinta is a small round, about 4” in diameter, weighing about 10oz. The interior texture is silky-smooth and the rind is fluffy, yet slightly firm with a Bay leaf embedded on the top. Made on the farm from our own pasteurized cows’ milk, the wheel is wrapped in Spruce bark that has been infused with the essence of CA Bay Laurel, which is indigenous to the region and ever-present on our farm in Point Reyes. Quinta is meant to be enjoyed at room temperature in a single sitting by removing a portion of the top rind and digging in with a small spoon or cheese spreader.

column1: Laubscher Cheese Company is a family-owned business and has been for over 60 years. They are not a manufacturer, but instead considered a cutting, shredding, and packaging company. column1: Made up of pasteurized cultured goat milk by Cypress Grove Chevre in the stunning and scenic rocky northern California and flavored with wild fennel and lavender pollen, the aromatic and herbaceous flavors of this fresh cheese confirm the Provencale/Mediterranean identity of Californian cuisine. column1: This is Brie-style cheese exclusively produced by Jasper Hill Farm, a creamery that not only makes cheeses but also offers cheese maturing caves for other Vermont based producers. It is named after Moses Sleeper, a Revolutionary War scout who was killed while defending Northeast Kingdom's Bayley Hazen Military Road. It has a classic bloomy rind with pink patches beneath which lies a gooey, milky core dotted with occasional eyes or holes. Moses is an approachable and nuanced brie-style cheese. Beneath its thin, bloomy rind lies a gooey, milky core showing a complex array of flavors at peak ripeness.

column1: With its blend of heat, umami, and nutty flavors, the key to the flavor is Shichimi Togarashi, a Japanese spice blend containing nori, toasted sesame, poppy and hemp seeds, chili flakes and ginger. The result is a gentle heat that warms your palate gradually, making you want more. This is a semi hard cheese with creamy texture and waxes rind. You will get butter notes with the classic Toma taste plus a gentle hit of umami heat and nutty undertones. TomaRashi is made from pasteurized, rBST-free cows’ milk and with microbial (vegetarian) rennet then aged for 90 days

column1: Ciliegine is Buf's smallest cheese. Meaning “cherry-sized” in Italian, this cheese comes in cherry tomato sized pieces. This size can be thrown atop a salad, served on a cheese plate, or eaten alone! Water buffalo milk is not only creamy and delicious, at BUF they go the extra mile to create a product that’s uniquely theirs. You can definitely taste the difference! The only non-GMO certified creamery in the world, they are proud leaders in responsibly produced water buffalo products. Through their trademark cheese making process, they have created a line of products that are lactose free, 100% vegetarian rennet, and rich in omega-3s. All our milk is A2.

column1: Calabro mozzarella is a type of fresh, soft cheese that is known for its mild, milky flavor and smooth, creamy texture. It is made from cow's milk and is a popular ingredient in many types of cuisine, particularly Italian and Mediterranean dishes. Calabro mozzarella is typically sold in ball-shaped form, and is made using traditional cheese-making methods. The cheese is stretched and kneaded by hand to create its distinctive texture and flavor, and is then immersed in brine to enhance its flavor and texture.

column1: Aged a minimum of four months, the bleu d'Auvergne displays a creamy ivory color with blueish green veins. With a moist and sticky rind, the cheese showcases assertive buttery, creamy, grassy flavors that shift to spicy, peppery and salty with age. Great used in salad dressings and pastas, the full-flavor of this cheese pairs well with a sweet dessert wine.

column1: A traditional, unpasteurized ewe's milk cheese from the picturesque mountains of Pyrenees that hold a fertile grazing land for the milk-giving ewes, this cheese unites two regions of France in the Western Pyrénées: Ossau valley of Bearn and Iraty Forest of Basque Country. It received an AOC protection in 1980, which requires that the cheese be produced with the milk of only two breeds of ewes - Manech and Basco-Béarnaise. An uncooked and pressed cheese, Ossau-Iraty is semi-hard in texture with a thick, buff rind marked with rust and grey moulds. Beneath the brown and orange rind is an ivory white, supple and slightly grainy interior that has a creamy and buttery mouth feel. Flavours are herbaceous, nutty and fruity if the produce is from winter while the summer cheeses tend to reveal aromas of grass and flowers.

column1: This Farmhouse Cheddar offers the wonderfully bright, buttery, and nutty flavors of a true English cheddar. Crafted with milk from grass-fed cows and traditional starter cultures, this cheese is simultaneously creamy and sharp with a pale yellow color. Try it in a grilled cheese on sourdough with a smear of apricot jam or let it take center stage on your next cheese board. Savile Row Cheese Co. represents a long tradition of English cheesemakers with the finest commitment to providing restauranteurs with products that not only enhance, but also elevate.

column1: A New England classic, this young cheddar is cold-smoked over maple and hardwood for up to four hours, imparting the signature aroma and satisfying flavor of this classic cheese. Grafton’s Maple Smoked Cheddar has a mild, buttery body with heady aromas of campfire and smoked ham. A sweet finish recalls memories of toasted marshmallows. This is a versatile cheese that can occupy nearly any culinary slot. Pair with dried apricots, pickled ramps, and cured meats for a cheese board. Maple Smoked Cheddar is a natural pairing with mustard and can add depth to a ham sandwich, melts superbly in any heated preparation.

column1: Buf burrata has an outer mozzarella cheese encasing a creamy interior of cows milk and water buffalo cream. Hand tied with our signature knot. Sprinkle with a little salt and olive oil and spread it on bread, crackers, or in caprese! Water buffalo milk is not only creamy and delicious, at BUF they go the extra mile to create a product that’s uniquely theirs. You can definitely taste the difference! The only non-GMO certified creamery in the world, they are proud leaders in responsibly produced water buffalo products. Through their trademark cheese making process, they have created a line of products that are lactose free, 100% vegetarian rennet, and rich in omega-3s. All our milk is A2.

column1: Philadelphia Original Cream Cheese traces its roots back to 1872, and it has been the standard of high quality cream cheese ever since. Today, it is made with five simple ingredients and is perfect for adding creaminess to recipes. You already love it for cheesecakes and dips, but be sure to give it a try for making creamy pasta sauce, delectable no-bake desserts, rich soups and much more. Local dairy farmers near Beaver Dam, WI and Lowville, NY supply Philly with fresh milk, which we combine with real cream. The entire process from farm to creamery takes just six days. But we don't stop at farm fresh milk and real cream. We also never add artificial preservatives, flavors or dyes in any of our cream cheese spreads. So in the end, everything just seems a little bit better with the creamy taste of Philly.

column1: Crafted with unparalleled expertise, our BUF Bufala Mozzarella is a celebration of authentic Italian tradition. Made from the finest buffalo milk sourced from local, free-roaming buffalo herds, every bite is a symphony of creamy richness and delicate flavors. Hand-stretched and shaped by skilled artisans, each luscious ball of mozzarella is a work of art, created with passion and precision. Its pristine white color and soft, supple texture speak volumes about the craftsmanship behind this artisanal delight. BUF Bufala Mozzarella pairs flawlessly with vibrant tomatoes, fresh basil, and a drizzle of premium olive oil for an unforgettable Caprese salad. Melt it over wood-fired pizzas, or elevate your pasta dishes to heavenly heights with its creamy goodness.

column1: Smithfield Bulk Cream Cheese is a premium quality dairy product that brings a rich, creamy taste and texture to your cooking and baking. This cream cheese is made from high-quality milk and cream that is carefully blended to create a smooth and velvety texture. Smithfield Bulk Cream Cheese is perfect for use in a wide variety of dishes, including dips, spreads, cheesecakes, and other baked goods. Its smooth and creamy texture makes it easy to spread and blend, while its rich flavor adds depth and complexity to your dishes.

column1: This flagship cheddar is made with raw cow’s milk and aged for two full years to achieve a mature flavor and dense, firm-yet-creamy texture. Young cheddar is tasted early on to determine the best trajectory for aging; for 2 Year Cheddar Grafton looks for balanced acidity and moisture that will hold up over time. This cheese bears the classical profile for New England cheddar: buttery notes with a bold, sharp tang and a long, nutty finish. The aroma is lactic and bright, with flavors of sweet cream.

column1: A soft blue-veined cheese. Made from fresh local cow's milk, it is handcrafted and aged 90 days in special caves. BelGioioso Master Cheesemakers hand-rub each wheel with salt and pierce small holes into the rind of the cheese, allowing air to penetrate, facilitating the growth of beneficial mold. This care and craft creates an exceptionally earthy flavor and creamy texture.

column1: Ciliegine is Buf's smallest cheese. Meaning “cherry-sized” in Italian, this cheese comes in cherry tomato sized pieces. This size can be thrown atop a salad, served on a cheese plate, or eaten alone! Water buffalo milk is not only creamy and delicious, at BUF they go the extra mile to create a product that’s uniquely theirs. You can definitely taste the difference! The only non-GMO certified creamery in the world, they are proud leaders in responsibly produced water buffalo products. Through their trademark cheese making process, they have created a line of products that are lactose free, 100% vegetarian rennet, and rich in omega-3s. All our milk is A2.

column1: Made from pasteurized cow’s milk and soft-ripened, its buttery flavor, silky texture and thin bloomy rind highlight the quality of our milk. Each wheel is individually handcrafted and ripened for two weeks before we hand wrap them for shipping. Green Hill is an eight-time winner at the American Cheese Society Annual Conference. When eating Green Hill by itself, the cheese is at its peak when allowed to warm up to room temperature. This gives the buttery paste a chance to soften and enhances the cheese's natural flavors. Green Hill is very easily melted so it is well suited to any dish needing some gooey deliciousness.

column1: This Part Skim Mozzarella Cheese Loaf brings a generous dose of refined Italian tradition to any pizza, salad, or creamy pasta dish. Crafted with farm-fresh skim milk from rBST-free cows and only all-natural ingredients, this mozzarella has a firm texture and a moderately creamy, slightly salty savory flavor. This part-skim variety boasts a lower butterfat and calorie content than a whole milk alternative, allowing for a beautiful melt when heated. Natural fermentation yields delightful buttery notes, perfect for loaded paninis and flatbreads.

column1: Also known as Five Territories is produced with pasteurized cow’s milk. The cheese is made by combining five English kinds of cheese namely, Cheddar, Cheshire, Derby, Double Gloucester, and Red Leicester. The alternating layers of yellow, orange, and white make this cheese visually stunning on a cheese platter. Since all five kinds of cheese are either Cheddar or close to Cheddar, the resulting cheese is mild and buttery in taste, smooth in texture with hints of salt.

column1: Burrata is an ultra soft cheese made from cow's milk. This cheese is made from fresh heavy cream and unspun mozzarella curds. The combined ingredients are placed into the center of a thin skin made from fresh mozzarella that is formed into a round shape, similar to a cloth bag. It has a rich, silky texture and the flavor is at once sweet and earthy with a slightly sour, yogurty backbone, as well as elusive hints of flowers and grass that linger on the palate.

column1: Sweet Grass Dairy's Griffin cheese is a semi-hard, cow's milk cheese that is aged for six months. It has a nutty and sweet flavor, with a smooth and creamy texture. This artisanal cheese is made using traditional methods and is handcrafted in small batches. It is perfect for adding to cheese boards, shredding over salads or pasta, or enjoying on its own with a glass of wine.

column1: Since 1855, generations of the Cravero family have been overseeing the staggionatura (cheese maturing) of the highest quality D.O.P Parmigiano-Reggiano. The Cravero family maintains cheese aging facilities both in Emilia Romagna and in the now famous town of Bra, home of Slow Food, where the family business has been headquartered for centuries.

column1: Dorset Drum is an authentic English Farmhouse Cheddar. It’s one of only a few Cheddars to carry the world renowned Protected Designation of Origin (PDO) status for Farmhouse Cheddar. Dorset Drum is made on a farm in Dorset, using milk from herds that graze on the lush, green pastures of the South West of England. Made to a unique recipe, using traditional handmade methods, Dorset Drum is a mature Cheddar with a full depth of flavour. An exceptional tasting Cheddar ideal for all occasions.

column1: An American original, made by Sebastian von Trapp on his family's dairy farm in Waitsfield, Vermont, this is an approachable washed-rind, tomme-style cheese. Oma is made from the organic milk of the von Trapp's primarily Jersey breed cows. Oma balances pungent and sweet flavors with aromas of roasted nuts, cured meat and cultured butter. The paste is soft, almost pudding-like, but never runny. The thin, orange rind, often overlaid with white flora, is an earthy foil to the richness of the paste.

column1: Parmesan cheese, as it is called in English, is considered to be among the top cheeses by cheese connoisseurs. Today, it is produced by various producers. However, PDO designation states that for a cheese to be called as Parmesan, it has to be produced from cows grazing on fresh grass and hay. Cheeses mocking Parmigiano Reggiano are called as Parmesan or Italian hard cheese by producers to avoid legal issues. Parmigiano Reggiano cheese is named after the provinces in which it is made, namely Provinces of Parma, Reggio Emilia, Modena, Bologna and Mantua. True Parmesan cheese has a hard, gritty texture and is fruity and nutty in taste.

column1: Made from 100% raw cow's milk in the regions of Reggio-Emilia, Modena and Parma, Parmigiano Reggiano is quite possibly Italy's most famous cheese. Mitica® Parmigiano Reggiano is sourced from a premium family of carefully selected farms. Farms are selected based on quality, artistry, location, and flavor profile. All wheels are aged a minimum of 24 months and receive extra testing during aging, receiving the coveted Export stamp by the Consorzio to further ensure the quality. Parmigiano Reggiano is an iconic cheese and when you choose Mitica®, you are choosing the best in class.

column1: This Dop Blue Cheese Is Made In The Artisan Tradition By Rural Dairy Farmers. Made Entirely From Cow'S Milk For Roughly 9 Months, It Is Made From A Blend Of Cow, Goat And Sheep'S Milk For The Remainder. All Of The Milk Used In The Production Must Come Exclusively From The Herds Raised In A Small Zone Of Production In Northern Spain. Cabrales Is Aged 2-6 Months In Natural Caves In The Mountains Nearby. It Has A Whiter, More Compact Texture When Young. When Mature, It Darkens In Color To Almost Grayish With More Blue Veining And Becomes Less Compact. It Has A Sharp, Spicy, Flavor With A Long Finish And Is Perfect For Those Who Like Their Blues With A Bite.

column1: Sugar Loaf Triple Creme is a soft and creamy cheese with a mild and buttery flavor. It is made from cow's milk and has a high butterfat content, making it rich and luxurious. The cheese has a bloomy rind and a soft, spreadable texture. Sugar Loaf Triple Creme is a versatile cheese that can be used in a variety of recipes, from appetizers to desserts, or simply enjoyed on its own with crackers or bread.

column1: Chaumes is a rather popular cheese among modern French varieties, in particular with children. column1: The ultimate melting cheese, there are few cheeses that go gooey as smoothly as Cabot’s lactose-free Monterey Jack. With its smooth, nutty flavor and distinctive taste, we like to think of this cheese as sharp cheddar’s mild-mannered cousin. Perfect for Southwestern-style cooking, it pairs beautifully with chilies and classic spices like cumin, cilantro, and paprika. Shred it over nachos for a photo-worthy appetizer or sprinkle it atop tacos for a creamy bite.

column1: This cheese is made with milk from pasture raised jersey cows infused with cream for a decadent balance of creamy and tangy herbaceous flavor. This cheese has a bloomy exterior, a buttery cream line, and a beautiful triple crème paste and is made with the milk of an exclusive herd of non-GMO jersey cows raised on pasture. A truly artisan cheese, made in small batches and cared for by hand at every stage at Nettle Meadow. Nettle Meadow is first and foremost a farm and animal sanctuary, with a culture of caring from the herd to the curd.

column1: Pont-l’Évêque cheese was created in the 12th century by Cistercian monks living near Caen, in Normandy. At the time, this cheese was known as “Angelot”, a term derived from the name of a coin that served as a means of exchange, remuneration and taxation!
